	<div id="dnn_ctr33855_HtmlModule_lblContent"><p><a class="btn btn-default" href="/Emergencies/NovelCoronavirusOutbreak2020COVID19/ChineseSimplified">‰∏≠Êñá&ndash; Chinese</a> <a class="btn btn-default" href="/Emergencies/NovelCoronavirusOutbreak2020COVID19/Korean">ÌïúÍµ≠Ïñ¥ &ndash; Korean</a> <a class="btn btn-default" href="/Emergencies/Coronavirus/Russian">–†—É—Å—Å–∫–∏–π &ndash; Russian</a> <a class="btn btn-default" href="/Emergencies/NovelCoronavirusOutbreak2020COVID19/CoronavirusSpanish">Espa√±ol - Spanish</a> <a class="btn btn-default" href="/Emergencies/NovelCoronavirusOutbreak2020COVID19/vietnamese">Ti·∫øng Vi·ªát &ndash; Vietnamese</a></p>

<div class="alert alert-info">
<h3 style="margin-top: 0px;"><strong><span class="fa fa-phone" style="margin-right: 7px;"><!-- not empty --></span> <span style="color: rgb(54, 81, 106);">Contact our Call Center</span></strong></h3>

<p><span style="color: rgb(54, 81, 106);">If you have questions about what is happening in Washington, or how the virus is spread, please call <strong>1-800-525-0127</strong> from 6 a.m. to 10 p.m, seven days a week. Please note that this call center can not access COVID-19 testing results.&nbsp;For&nbsp;testing inquiries or&nbsp;results, please contact your health care provider.&nbsp;</span></p>
</div>

<p>On January 21, 2020, the Centers for Disease Control and Prevention (CDC) and Washington State Department of Health announced the first case of 2019 Novel Coronavirus (COVID-19) in the United States in Washington State.</p>

<p>This guidance does not pertain to Gov. Jay Inslee&rsquo;s Stay Home, Stay Healthy order issued 3/23/2020. Information on that order is available on the <a href="https://medium.com/wagovernor/inslee-announces-stay-home-stay-healthy-order-4891a7511f5e">Governor&#39;s website</a>.</p>

<p>Learn more about the coronavirus from Washington State&rsquo;s <a href="http://www.coronavirus.wa.gov/">official COVID-19 website</a>. Maintained by the state&nbsp;<a href="https://www.coronavirus.wa.gov/about" title="About">Joint Information Center</a>.</p>

<h2>Current Status in Washington State</h2>

<div style="background:#eee;border:1px solid #ccc;padding:5px 10px;">Please note that we have shifted our reporting process to make it more accurate, timely and complete. We are reporting confirmed cases, laboratory tests and deaths as of the previous day at 11:59 pm PT.</div>

<p style="text-align: center;"><br />
<strong>Last updated 11:59pm 3/31/2020</strong></p>

<p>&nbsp;</p>

 <p style="text-align: left;font-weight:normal;font-size:80%">Data is now available for total case counts by county for March 29, 30, and 31.</p>

 <p style="text-align: left;font-weight:normal;font-size:80%">Due to incomplete data for date of deaths on a number of deaths we are unable to provide the daily death counts for March 29th and 30th. <p><strong>Note on the county and unassigned data:</strong> This data&nbsp;changes rapidly as labs conduct tests and discover new cases. Labs assign those cases to a county. Counties or the Department of Health then determine the appropriate county of jurisdiction. Those don&rsquo;t always match initially. We&rsquo;re working to reduce the &ldquo;unassigned&rdquo; number to 0. Contact the local health department for county specific information.</p>

<p><strong>Note on the deaths:</strong> Some deaths may be reported by health care providers, medical examiners/coroners, local health departments, or others before they are included in the statewide count. It takes longer for the state to announce deaths because they are often reported first to the local health department and then to us.</p>

<p><strong>Note on the number of infections:</strong> Public health experts agree that the true number of people who have been infected with COVID-19 in Washington greatly exceeds the number of COVID-19 infections that have been laboratory-confirmed. It is very difficult to know exactly how many people in Washington have been infected to date since most people with COVID-19 experience mild illness and the ability to get tested is still not widely available.</p>
